Release 1 Plan
Pronzo
Pronzo Developers
Capellini
Release: 04 - 10 - 2017
v1.0.0
Revision: 04 - 19 - 2017

High Level Goals
Create a usable application
Create user profiles with user information, food preferences, and interests
Linkedin or .edu email logins only
Create a post board for meet ups with the intention of adding a map linked to the posts
Deploy a restaurant database for users to easily choose from restaurants near them
Allow users to filter age, food preferences, and interests
Allow companies to post ads on the application

User Stories for Release
Sprint 1
As a user, I want an application that can connect me with professionals so that I can build connections within my industry  (21)
As a user, I want a login in with Linkedin or .edu email logins only to ensure a safe login system (2)
As a user, I want to be able to build a profile so professionals can see if they are interested in connecting with me. (3)
As a user, I want to see when and where other like-minded professionals are planning to go to lunch so that I can schedule meetings (8)
Sprint 2
As a user, I want to view a map to see the locations of other userâ€™s meeting posts so I can know how close others are to me. (5)
As a user, I need to be able to quickly and easily communicate with someone I am meeting with so that we can better coordinate (specific) times and locations.  (13)
As a developer, I want to use the Yelp API with the search bar to make their restaurant database available (3)
As a user I want an auto-completion/auto-suggestion feature so I do not have to type a specific restaurant but a style of food and receive results (5)
Sprint 3
As a user, I want to report dangerous activity so that I do not have spam activity on my interface (5)
As a user I want to be able to filter various categories to create an event feed more catered to my preferences.(5)


Product Backlog
Companies submitting ads for meal discounts 
As a marketer, I want people using the app to go eat at my restaurant. (13)
